Vortix - Project Outline
(Cryptocurrency Analytics Dashboard)
This is a quick technical overview of the tools, APIs, and libraries used to build the NeoCrypto analytics platform.
1. Data Sources (APIs)
•
Crypto Market Data: CoinGecko API
o
Used for: Real-time cryptocurrency prices, market cap rankings, historical chart data, and top gainers/losers.
o
Endpoints used: /coins/markets, /coins/{id}/market_chart.
•
Artificial Intelligence: Google Gemini API
o
Used for: The "NeoAI Assistant" chatbot.
o
Function: Analyzes current market data context to provide summary insights and answer user questions.
2. Visualization (Graphs & Charts)
•
Library: Recharts
•
Chart Types Implemented:
o
Area Chart: Default view for price history (visualizes trends with a gradient fill).
o
Line Chart: Used for clean price tracking and comparison overlays.
o
Bar Chart: Option for viewing discrete price points over time.
•
Features: Custom tooltips, responsive resizing, and multiple axes for coin comparisons.
3. UI Assets (Icons & Styling)
•
Icons: Lucide React
o
A clean, consistent icon set used for navigation (LayoutDashboard, Wallet), actions (Trash2, Plus), and indicators (TrendingUp, Activity).
•
Styling Framework: Tailwind CSS
o
Primary Styling Engine: Used for rapid UI development with utility classes.
o
Theme: Implements a specific "Neon Dark Mode" aesthetic (#FF5F1F accent on #000000 background).
o
Capabilities: Handles Flexbox/Grid layouts, responsive breakpoints, and visual effects like Glassmorphism (backdrop-blur) and neon glows (drop-shadow).
4. Backend & Authentication
•
Platform: supabase
o
Authentication: Manages secure user sign-up, sign-in, profile image managing and session handling (e.g., Email/Password).
o
Data Persistence: Uses Firestore to save user-specific data, ensuring portfolios and watchlists are synced across devices.
5. Core Framework
•
Frontend Library: React (v18+)
•
Build Tool: Vite
•
State Management: React Hooks (useState, useEffect, useMemo, useRef) for managing portfolio state, API data fetching, and UI toggles.
